<br>
However, even in a perfect world where employers didn't make that assumption (and I know that some do), you'd still find that due to the actual attrition rates of women who do reproduce, you are going to always see something less than 50% of top management be women. <br>
<br>
It's just reality. It's not wrong or right, it's nature. Again, let me reiterate that it is wrong for an employer to make the decision FOR a woman by precluding their inclusion in management -- but then the question becomes, is there therefore a compelling state interest to impose government quotas on private business due to the possibility? I think the answer is no.<br>
<br>
The market will rule; employers who do this are stupid and will make less money than those who don't make this mistake -- and there are more and more employers who understand this. <br>
