ill wants to work an abbreviated week so she is forced to turn down the position.  They create a new manager position (some here would argue that this position is bogus) and slide her quota into a corresponding new cost center.  The director position comes out of our section's quota (in effect, we've lost a quota).  As I'm sure you will agree, there were many concessions made during this entire process.  This is a good sized company of about 24k employees and this is the only person that I have ever heard of swinging this kind of deal.  What does everyone think about this?  Was this fair?  Would they have done it for a man that wanted to spend more time with his children?  Would they have done it for anyone that wasn't in management?  I don't know, but at any rate it's a pretty slick maneuver.  I'd probably do it if I could. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showPrevMessage?topicID=918.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showNextMessage?topicID=918.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=918.topic&index=77><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/fr/themes/default/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.threadControl?topicID=918.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/fr/themes/default/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=918.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=918.